- The tricky part (for opengl) is to store an array of roots
- - For simplicity, assume we tested that a root exist or just know it):
- - - this is done by testing where your function WOULD BE undefined:
- - - - check if any divisor==0.;
- - - - check if log(a) has an a<=0;
- - - - check if pow(a,b) has any a==.0 AND B==.0 //
- - - - check if pow(a,b) has any a<0. AND  0.<abs(b)<1. (still doable with complex numbers)
- - - - ... + anything else where your axiomes are incomplete or inconsistent (or both)
- - - the problem os assuming that a root exists where there is none is that your function is not defined there.
- 2 non parallel coplanar lines have 1 root
- a line and a non-tangential circle/ellipse/parabola/QuadraticFunction
- .... has 2 roots.  it has 1 root if it is tangential.
- ...
- This shader solves roots for a QuadraticFunction==bezier.
